ok heres what i think 
cause i am out of ideas also we have fixed all sorts of things.
It has had a slick fan belt for quiet sometime before i bought the dual carbs and put on it.
When i would go to adjust the valves and try to turn the bolt on the alternator i would have to physically grab the belt by hand as i turned the bolt to get it to turn and then sometimes i like on the 180 i could turn the motor with just the wrench.
"Reason"= the oil was slick on the belt causing it to slide when turning the bolt.
No friction .........
i never noticed the oil dripping under the bus till later on but dont think it was till after the duals got put on?
it has always had a qaurter size drip coming from the tranny and engine where they were mated even though we used all new seals. That was fine by me and is a normal spot for a tiny drip as that and she is just marking her spot.
The small drip that started under the fan housing on the ground i never could locate though; the one that was making fan belt slick and causing the oil drip under the fan housing armor.
 
Well when the duals were put on the engine was run real hot that day trying to adjust the linkage and my fears is this is what could of made the rings etc... go bad?causing blowby?
there again was the oil already blowing out of the dipstick hole slightly? causing the slick fan belt and wetness there in the belly of the fan armor?
the overheating of the engine must of made it worse?(duals installed that day)
 
thing is the oil spliage this bad didnt start till i decided i no longer wanted to run the duals
they gave me a fit and i didnt have the power i needed so michael mentions the power loss i had and thats true i just couldnt get them right and someone else mentioned about the jet sizes.???? hmmm the duals made me appreciate a weber but thats just me call me lazy if you will i call it being simple.(grins)
 
so i took them off and have traded a friend for another weber but in the meantime i am borrowing the carb off the club engine in order to puut putt round town for work and other thing trying to make to money and then school pick up and drop off and such.

