was a normal day to me and didnt race the bus there never get on her she's my baby and i treat her right nice and slow (SLOW VEHICLE=PASS WITH CAUTION)reads across the back  bumper in  large 4 inch letters ... {{{{{no joke go around bung hole head should of left ealrier or as expected as much(YOURE BEHIND A 76 VW BUS 55 stay alive)!
 
{{{{{ok so thats the first notice that i had lost a great deal of oil}}}}}}}(it was all over the ground under the bus) since rebuild motor wasnt using oil at all except maybe every 500 miles i would put a drop in her 1/4 of a qaurt had the same qaurt for awhile.
 
i got home and cleaned her up and put about a half qaurt maybe a little less than half qaurt>?close....
ok so the leak went to minimal for a bit afterwards?
 
then the leak came back again?
phil drove up  we messed with the oil filler cap and it stopped leaking like that and a few other things as well.
made sure everything was right and readjusted timing again.
(anything you remember we did here i forgot to mention phil?)
 
the leak started back and was chunking up some oil and phil came back up last week and we did compression test and everything turned out good.
we also replaced the oil sender on the top of the crank case and plugged off the oil dipstick hole with a piece of gas line and bolt.
 
the  leak stopped.
after a day of driving it::: i was bound and determined to figure this out.
i didnt want to have to carry my dipstick around with me it needed to be in the shoot and why is it coming out of the dipstick and how do i fix it now?????
 
so i cleaned the oil breather soaking it in gasoline for 3 hours shaking it every 15 minutes of three hours.
all sorts of black junk came out of it each time i shook it.
 
i blew through it and had lots of air coming through even soaked the top pvc valve with it  and off of it unattached made sure it was cleaned out.
dried and put back on bus sealed up good and still oil everywhere>?
i can see it running down under the metal tube from the dipstick. A actual stream of oil under the tube and it is flowing from there to down in the belly of the fan armor and tin and out onto the ground.
 
ok so i take a piece of gas line and attach it on there and then take a piece of gas line that is as big as the biggest round part that stops the dipstick from going in the tube its's self.
it seals it up tight fit and it bottoms out on the metal tube and gives accurate oil reaind on the level line, buttttttttttt when i go take my daughter to school and come back home the smell of oil lubricates the air in the carport as i exit and i look and yep same spot its the size of a soda can already??? dark black oil and i open the hatch to see where its coming from since it was all cleaned up before hand.
you can see the oil streaks on the new gas line to seal off the dipstick looks like the barrel of a firecracker once blow up but yet with oil. and its dripping from the alternator end again and all over the back side of the tin foam seal and in the belly of the tin under the fan armor.
 
then i came to my wits and have parked her till i can get a new/ used oil breather to try my luck in case its my oil breather thats messed up or still clogged.
If that doesnt work i will get a leak down test kit maybe got to check around today for a price on one so more than likely that will have to wait.
